# Day 89 — Create the Home Screen (Navigation Hub)

**Time:** ~1 hour

## Goal

Instead of launching directly into the Dashboard, the app should first show a **Home Screen** where users can choose what they want to do.

The Home Screen will have four options:

```
Blood Report App

👤 Upload Report

📄 My Reports

📊 Dashboard

⚙ Settings
```

For now, these buttons will simply navigate to the existing screens.

---

# Step 1

Create a new file:

```
lib/screens/home_screen.dart
```

Replace the entire file with:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

import 'all_reports_screen.dart';
import 'post_test_screen.dart';

class HomeScreen extends StatelessWidget {
  const HomeScreen({super.key});

  Widget buildButton(
      BuildContext context,
      IconData icon,
      String title,
      Widget page,
      Color color,
      ) {

    return SizedBox(

      width: double.infinity,

      height: 70,

      child: ElevatedButton.icon(

        icon: Icon(icon,size:30),

        label: Text(

          title,

          style: const TextStyle(
            fontSize:20,
          ),

        ),

        style: ElevatedButton.styleFrom(
          backgroundColor: color,
          foregroundColor: Colors.white,
        ),

        onPressed: () {

          Navigator.push(

            context,

            MaterialPageRoute(
              builder: (_) => page,
            ),

          );

        },

      ),

    );

  }

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {

    return Scaffold(

      appBar: AppBar(

        title: const Text("Blood Report App"),

        centerTitle: true,

      ),

      body: Padding(

        padding: const EdgeInsets.all(20),

        child: Column(

          children: [

            const SizedBox(height:20),

            buildButton(

              context,

              Icons.upload_file,

              "Upload Report",

              const PostTestScreen(),

              Colors.blue,

            ),

            const SizedBox(height:20),

            buildButton(

              context,

              Icons.description,

              "My Reports",

              const AllReportsScreen(),

              Colors.green,

            ),

            const SizedBox(height:20),

            buildButton(

              context,

              Icons.dashboard,

              "Dashboard",

              const AllReportsScreen(),

              Colors.orange,

            ),

            const SizedBox(height:20),

            buildButton(

              context,

              Icons.settings,

              "Settings",

              const Placeholder(),

              Colors.grey,

            ),

          ],

        ),

      ),

    );

  }

}
```

---

# Step 2

Replace your **entire** `lib/main.dart` with:

```dart
import 'package:flutter/material.dart';

import 'screens/home_screen.dart';

void main() {

  runApp(const MyApp());

}

class MyApp extends StatelessWidget {

  const MyApp({super.key});

  @override
  Widget build(BuildContext context) {

    return MaterialApp(

      debugShowCheckedModeBanner: false,

      title: 'Blood Report App',

      home: const HomeScreen(),

    );

  }

}
```

---

# Step 3

Run the app:

```bash
flutter run -d chrome
```

or build a new APK:

```bash
flutter build apk
```

